summary:
The problem Source: Codewars Create a RomanNumerals class that can convert a roman numeral to and from an integer value.
#include &lt;string&gt; #include &lt;vector&gt; class RomanHelper{ public: std::string to_roman(unsigned int n){ } int from_roman(std::string rn){ } } RomanNumerals; It should follow the API demonstrated in the examples below. Multiple roman numeral values will be tested for each helper method.
Modern Roman numerals are written by expressing each digit separately starting with the left most digit and skipping any digit with a value of zero.
